column1: Students Should Learn Fewer Topics In Greater Depth Instead of Learning More Topics In Less Depth In An Introductory Statistics Course
column2: Basic Rules of Probability Should Be Included In An Introductory Statistics Course
column3: The Topic of Theoretical Probability Distributions e.g. The Binomial Distribution Should Be Included In An Introductory Statistics Course
column4: Students Should Learn How to Read Statistical Tables of Probability Distributions e.g. T Table Z Table
column5: Students Should Learn The Importance of Using Appropriate Methods For Collecting Data
column6: Students Should Learn Connections Between The Qualityture of The Data and Inferences that Are Made
column7: Technology Tools Should Be Used to Illustrate Most Abstract Statistical Concepts
column8: Students Should Analyze Data Primarily Using Technology
column9: Lectures Should Be The Primary Way For Students to Learn Statistical Content
column10: Quizzes and Exams Should Be Used As The Primary Way to Evaluate Student Learning
column11: Alternative Assessments e.g. Projects Presentations Should Be Used to Provide Important Information About Student Learning
column12: All Assessments Should Be Regularly Reviewed to See that They Are Aligned With Student Learning Goals
column13: Formative Feedback Should Be Given On All Assessments In Order For Students to Improve Their Learning
column14: Students Should Be Assessed On Their Ability to Complete An Open Ended Statistical Problem
column15: Students Should Be Assessed On Their Statistical Literacy e.g. Ability to Read a Graph Understand Common Statistical Words etc.
column16: Statistics Courses Should Be Updated Continually to Keep Up With Advances In Technology
column17: Statistics Courses Should Be Updated Continually In Response to Recommendations Such As Common Core
column18: Statistics Instructors Should Be Actively Engaged In The Statistics Education Community
column19: The Content Was Presented Mostly Through Lectures
column20: The Instructor Asked Challenging Questions that Made Students Think
column21: The Course Frequently Required Students to Work Together
column22: The Content Was Presented Mostly Through Activities
column23: this Course Encouraged Students to Discover Ideas On Their Own
column24: Students Use Graphing Calculators Regularly In this Course
column25: this Course Often Used Technology Other Than Graphing Calculators to Help Students Understand Concepts
